The animals prints are a natural progression of my life as a mom.  My son and I spend many hours discussing, looking at, sounding out, and getting excited about animals. 

One morning, as Remy sat in his highchair, I showed him some of my new  paintings.  He studied them, and held his little face close to the paper, and then he smiled and clapped.  I remembered why I love making art, especially for kids.  I love the idea of happy paintings that encourage imagination, surrounding our kiddos as they grow up.  I also want the images to be available and affordable to everyone, so a switch to downloadable prints seemed the best way to make that happen.

Your purchase comes with four files: a 5x7 JPG & PDF, and an 8x10 JPG & PDF.  This should cover any printing needs in a photo or print lab.  

As always, you are welcome to print as many copies as you'd like for yourself and to use as gifts, but please do not share the files via email or sell the printed product for money.  Do not alter the files in any way.

Take a photo of your prints new home or journey and pin, instagram, twitter with the hashtag #ashmaedotcom.

Thank you and enjoy!

description:

I've had so many people request custom sizes and large orders of temple prints, I thought I'd turn over the details of  to my customers.
